        <div class="hero">
            <div class="heroTitle">
                <h1 class="mainTitle">Dylan Hanwell</h1>
                <h1 class="subMainTitle">For President</h1>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="about" class="section">
            <div class="content">
                <h2>About <span class="feature-color">Dylan</span></h2>
                <img src="/images/headshpt.png" width=400/>
                <p>
                    Hi, I’m Dylan and I’m running to be the President of your Students’ Union.

                    Over the last year I’ve been working as your VP External where I advocated to all levels of government

                    for things like student jobs, tuition, and mental health funding.

                    I want to make school more affordable, build student community from the ground up, and raise revenue

                    for the SU without increasing fees.

                    University needs to stay affordable and to do that, I will be advocating for an affordable U-Pass in our

                    upcoming negotiations, working with the next VPX to rollback tuition, and lobbying for more student

                    grants.

                    Students build student community. This has been forgotten in past years and to ensure this I will be

                    advocating that Residence Associations be able to collect fees, and control of student groups into the

                    hands of the SU.

                    In my term, I will find ways to increase the revenue of the SU outside fees; this means the development

                    of an alumni endowment fund, filling all retail spaces in SUB, and improving our businesses.

                    Finally, I won’t pretend to know everything you care about, so thats why I am allowing you to add your own idea below or If you just want to chat you can email me at hanwell@ualberta.ca
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="platform" class="section">
            <div class="content">
                <h1>Platform</h1>
                <p>My platform focuses on four themes.</p>

                <p class="platform-point">
                    1 The U- Pass has been a highly successful and popular fee for students at the U of A. If elected, I will make sure that as we go into negotiations for the renewal of the U-Pass, it remains affordable at a sustainable cost to students.
                </p>
                <p class="platform-point">
                    2 Residence Associations and residents need a strong voice advocating for their right to collect fees and their rights as tenants, respectively. If elected, I will advocate for Residence Associations to retain the ability to collect fees and a resident rights framework.
                </p>
                <p class="platform-point">
                    3 The Students’ Union must make sure that the businesses it runs add value to campus and stay relevant to students. If elected, I will work within the Students’ Union to improve the relevance of our businesses to students.

                </p>
                <p class="platform-point">
                    4 I don't have all the answers, and my final promise is to listen to you! If you have an idea that you would like to see on campus or want to see other student-submitted ideas click <a target="_blank" href="http://votedylan.idea.informer.com/">here!</a> This way the community can come together on a goal.
                </p><br/>
                <p>For those interested, I do have longer versions of my platform beyond what is provided above:<br />
                <p class="center"><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1dLNuXxhElxLGV-buSX7mUSmEq-r_UWgFZjTOIqZb9uw/edit">Medium Length (2 pages)</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="get-involved" class="section">
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Get Involved</h2>
                <p>Check out my <a href="https://twitter.com/dylanhanwell">Twitter</a>, and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/votedylan/">Facebook</a> accounts for daily updates.</p>
                <p>If you want to get closer to the action of the campaign and volunteer, feel free to send me a message and let you know what you would like to get involved with! As well, if you have a burning question you would like to ask or just talk, send me a message through the form below or via Facebook or Twitter</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="contact" class="section">
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Contact <span id="form-message" class="message"></span></h2>

                <form method="POST" action="/send" id="form">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="email">Your Email</label>
                        <input type="email" class="form-control" name="email" id="email" placeholder="Your Email" required />
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="name">Your Name</label>
                        <input type="text" class="form-control" name="name" id="name" placeholder="Your Name" required />
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="message">Your Message</label>
                        <textarea class="form-control" name="message" rows="3" required></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group clobber">
                        <label for="website">Website</label>
                        <input type="text" class="form-control" name="website" id="website" placeholder="Your Website" />
                    </div>

                    <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>">
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
